place.name: BEELSBY
place.gazetteerText: BEELSBY, a parish in Caistor district, Lincoln; 5 miles E of Caistor, and 6½ W of Waltham r. station. Post Town, Caistor. Acres, 2,189. Real property, £3,692. Pop., 181. Houses, 33. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £450. Patron, the Collegiate Church of Southwell. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
